Japanese Bought Net 973.3 Billion Yen Overseas Debt Last Week

-- B y   T h e r e s a   B a r r a c l o u g h
-- 
2011-03-30T23:54:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-30/japanese-bought-net-973-3-billion-yen-overseas-debt-last-week.html
Japanese investors were net
buyers of foreign bonds during the week ended March 25 according to
figures based on reports from designated major investors released by
the Ministry of Finance in  Tokyo .  Japanese investors bought 973.3 billion yen ($11.7 billion)
in overseas bonds and notes, sold 33.8 billion yen in overseas stocks
and sold 17.1 billion yen in overseas short term securities.
That results in a total net purchase of 922.4 billion yen.  Foreign investors sold 93.8 billion yen in Japanese bonds,
sold 13.3 billion yen in stocks, and sold 1112.5 billion yen in
short term securities, resulting in a total net sale 1219.7
billion yen.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Theresa Barraclough in Tokyo at   tbarraclough@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Marco Babic at   mbabic@bloomberg.net  